# CODEOWNERS for bold-minds/mcp-ynab
#
# When a PR modifies a file, GitHub will auto-request a review from the
# listed owners. Path patterns are evaluated in order, and the LAST matching
# pattern wins — so the general owner line stays at the top and the more
# specific security-sensitive rules come after.
#
# Replace the placeholder owners below with your actual GitHub username or
# team before enabling branch protection that requires code-owner review.

# Default owner for everything in the repo.
* @bold-minds/maintainers

# Security-critical paths — these files touch the credential handling path
# or the outbound HTTP path. Any change requires explicit security review.
/token.go             @bold-minds/maintainers @bold-minds/security
/client.go            @bold-minds/maintainers @bold-minds/security
/errors.go            @bold-minds/maintainers @bold-minds/security
/main.go              @bold-minds/maintainers @bold-minds/security

# CI and release infrastructure — supply-chain risk, requires maintainer review.
/.github/             @bold-minds/maintainers
/Dockerfile           @bold-minds/maintainers
/.goreleaser.yaml     @bold-minds/maintainers
/go.mod               @bold-minds/maintainers
/go.sum               @bold-minds/maintainers

# Documentation can land with a single maintainer review.
/README.md            @bold-minds/maintainers
/SECURITY.md          @bold-minds/maintainers @bold-minds/security
/CHANGELOG.md         @bold-minds/maintainers
/CONTRIBUTING.md      @bold-minds/maintainers
/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md   @bold-minds/maintainers
